<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-A">A</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-AccesscontrolAccesscontrol"><strong> <span class=3D"conf=
luence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Accesscontrol"></span> </strong>Access c=
ontrol</h4>
<p>The mechanism of granting and prohibiting access to different parts of t=
he website; see <a href=3D"#Glossary-Policy">Policy</a>, <a href=3D"#Glossa=
ry-Role">Role</a>, <a href=3D"#Glossary-Accessfunction">Access function</a>=
, <a href=3D"#Glossary-User">User</a>, <a href=3D"#Glossary-Usergroup">User=
 group</a>.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Managing+permiss=
ions">Managing permissions</a>.</p>
<p>More information (Technical Manual): <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/displa=
y/DEVELOPER/Repository#Repository-Permissions" rel=3D"nofollow">Permissions=
</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-AccessfunctionAccessfunction"><strong> <span class=3D"co=
nfluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Accessfunction"></span> </strong>Acces=
s function</h4>
<p>The smallest element of the <a href=3D"#Glossary-Accesscontrol">permissi=
ons </a>system: a single component of a <a href=3D"#Glossary-Policy">policy=
</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ActionbarActionbar"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-lin=
k" id=3D"Glossary-Actionbar"></span>Action bar</h4>
<p>A menu in the right pane of the <a href=3D"#Glossary-Contentmode">Conten=
t mode</a>. It allows you to create, modify and manipulate Content.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-AttributeAttribute"><span style=3D"color: rgb(153,153,15=
3);"> <strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Attrib=
ute"></span> </strong> </span> <em>Attribute</em></h4>
<p>Legacy term for <a href=3D"#Glossary-FieldType">Field Type</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-B">B</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-BlockBlock"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D=
"Glossary-Block"></span>Block</h4>
<p>The basic segment of a <a href=3D"#Glossary-LandingPage">Landing Page</a=
>. Blocks can be placed on a Landing Page using drag-and-drop and later cus=
tomized.</p>
<p class=3D"confluence-link">More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/dis=
play/USER/Adding+blocks+to+Landing+Page">Adding blocks to Landing Page</a>.=
</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-BundleBundle"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-=
link" id=3D"Glossary-Bundle"></span> </strong>Bundle</h4>
<p>A directory containing a set of files (PHP files, stylesheets, JavaScrip=
ts, images, etc.) that implement a single feature (for example a blog or a =
forum). This is a term used in <a href=3D"#Glossary-Symfony">Symfony</a>, w=
hich distributes both its main framework and extensions or addins in the fo=
rm of bundles.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-C">C</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-CLACLA"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" =
id=3D"Glossary-CLA"></span> </strong>CLA</h4>
<p>Contributor Licensing Agreement. An agreement which needs to be signed b=
efore contributing to the development of eZ.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-CMSCMS"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" =
id=3D"Glossary-CMS"></span> </strong>CMS</h4>
<p>Content Management System. This is the basic type of software that eZ of=
fers.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-CXMCXM"><strong> <em> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-l=
ink" id=3D"Glossary-CXM"></span> </em> </strong>CXM</h4>
<p>Customer Experience Management. The whole of marketing and business acti=
vities, processes and tools connected with interaction between a company an=
d its customers.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-CloudServicesCloudServices"><span class=3D"confluence-an=
chor-link" id=3D"Glossary-CloudServices"></span>Cloud Services</h4>
<p>A commercial component of eZ with options for gathering and using conten=
t intelligence, including capabilities such as recommendations or marketing=
 automation.</p>
<p>Cloud Services is also available as a standalone solution.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ClusteringClustering"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence=
-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Clustering"></span> </strong>Clustering</h4>
<p>The way of setting up an installation to have several web servers runnin=
g eZ.</p>
<p>More information (Technical Manual): <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Clust=
ering">Clustering</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-CommunityCommunity"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-a=
nchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Community"></span> </strong>Community</h4>
<p>The <a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofol=
low">Community Gateway</a> for eZ users. Also, the open-source version of t=
he <a href=3D"#Glossary-eZPublishCommunity">previous generation </a>of eZ p=
roducts.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ComponentsComponents"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-l=
ink" id=3D"Glossary-Components"></span> <em>Components</em></h4>
<p>A library of independent components for Web applications. In the current=
 versions of eZ replaced by <a href=3D"#Glossary-Twig">Twig </a>templates a=
nd <a href=3D"#Glossary-Symfony">Symfony </a> <a href=3D"#Glossary-Bundle">=
bundles</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ComposerComposer"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anc=
hor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Composer"></span> </strong>Composer</h4>
<p>A PHP packaging system to manage dependencies. It is used in the install=
ation and update mechanism of eZ. See&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://getcomposer.o=
rg/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://getcomposer.org/</a>.=
</p>
<p>More information (Technical Manual): <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Using=
+Composer">Using Composer</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ContentContentitems"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-=
anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Content"></span>Content items</strong></h4>
<p><strong>1.</strong> In the broad sense, content items is everything that=
 is placed on a site for the visitor to see.</p>
<p><strong>2.</strong> (<em>sing</em>. a Content item, <em>Pl.</em> Content=
 items) In the narrow sense, a Content item is a single object used on a si=
te. It can be, for example, an article, a photo gallery or a blog post. Tec=
hnically, a Content item is an instance of a <a href=3D"#Glossary-ContentTy=
pe">Content Type</a> (that is, it is a single object created on the basis o=
f a "blueprint" which is the Content Type).</p>
<p>Occasionally, the term "regular Content" is used to refer to any type of=
 Content other than a<a href=3D"#Glossary-LandingPage"> Landing Page</a>.</=
p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Fundamental+conc=
epts">Fundamental concepts</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ContentClassContentClass"><span class=3D"confluence-anch=
or-link" id=3D"Glossary-ContentClass"></span> <em>Content Class</em></h4>
<p>Legacy term for <a href=3D"#Glossary-ContentType">Content Type</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ContentmodeContentmode"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor=
-link" id=3D"Glossary-Contentmode"></span>Content mode</h4>
<p>The editing mode used in eZ Platform. The Content mode concentrates on c=
reating, editing and managing Content items.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=
=3D32113236">Content mode interface(old)</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ContentstateContentstate"><strong> <span class=3D"conflu=
ence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Contentstate"></span> </strong>Content sta=
te</h4>
<p>The status of a Content item version. Each version can have the status o=
f Draft (created but not published yet), Published or Archived (removed or =
replaced by a newer version).</p>
<p>See also <a href=3D"#Glossary-Contentversioning">Content versioning</a>.=
</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ContenttreeContenttree"><strong> <span class=3D"confluen=
ce-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Contenttree"></span> </strong>Content tree</=
h4>
<p>The structure into which Content is organized in the system.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ContentTypeContentType"><strong> <span class=3D"confluen=
ce-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-ContentType"></span> </strong>Content Type</=
h4>
<p>A template or blueprint for <a href=3D"#Glossary-Content">Content</a>. I=
t defines <a href=3D"#Glossary-Field">Fields </a>and their <a href=3D"#Glos=
sary-FieldType">Field Types</a> which are then assigned <a href=3D"#Glossar=
y-FieldValue">Field Values</a> when a Content item is created based on this=
 Content Type.</p>
<p>Content Type is conceptually similar to a class in object-oriented progr=
amming.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide):&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/USER/Content+Typ=
es">Content Types</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ContentversioningContentversioning"><strong> <span class=
=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Contentversioning"></span> </str=
ong>Content versioning</h4>
<p>A control mechanism for changes made to content. Whenever a piece of <a =
href=3D"#Glossary-Content">Content </a>is modified, its previous version is=
 preserved with an Archived state. You can view an earlier version of Conte=
nt and revert to it if you decide to undo the changes.</p>
<p>See also <a href=3D"#Glossary-Contentstate">Content state</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-CSSCSS"><em> <strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-l=
ink" id=3D"Glossary-CSS"></span> </strong> </em>CSS</h4>
<p>Cascading Style Sheets used to create and apply styles to websites. Can =
be used in conjunction with <a href=3D"#Glossary-Twig">Twig</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-D">D</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-DataTypeDataType"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link"=
 id=3D"Glossary-DataType"></span> <em>Data Type</em></h4>
<p>Legacy term for <a href=3D"#Glossary-FieldType">Field Type</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-DemoBundleDemoBundle"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence=
-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-DemoBundle"></span> </strong>Demo Bundle</h4>
<p>A bundle containing a demonstration version of a website created using e=
Z. You can use it to familiarize yourself with the system, or to create you=
r own website on its basis.</p>
<p>There is a separate Demo Bundle for eZ Platform and eZ Enterprise.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Demo+Bundle">Dem=
o Bundle</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-DiscoverybarDiscoverybar"><span class=3D"confluence-anch=
or-link" id=3D"Glossary-Discoverybar"></span>Discovery bar</h4>
<p>A menu in the left pane of the <a href=3D"#Glossary-Contentmode">Content=
 mode</a>. It allows you to navigate the repository.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-DynamicpageDynamicpage"><strong> <span class=3D"confluen=
ce-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Dynamicpage"></span> </strong>Dynamic page</=
h4>
<p>One of the types of <a href=3D"#Glossary-LandingPage">Landing Page</a>: =
a page with dynamically generated content.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-E">E</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ExtensionExtension"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-lin=
k" id=3D"Glossary-Extension"></span> <em>Extension</em></h4>
<p>Legacy term for <a href=3D"#Glossary-Bundle">Bundle</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-eZEnterpriseeZEnterprise"><span class=3D"confluence-anch=
or-link" id=3D"Glossary-eZEnterprise"></span>eZ Enterprise</h4>
<p>The current commercial stack of eZ. It contains the open-source <a href=
=3D"#Glossary-eZPlatform">eZ Platform</a> component as well as <a href=3D"#=
Glossary-Studio">Studio</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-eZPlatformeZPlatform"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence=
-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-eZPlatform"></span> </strong>eZ Platform</h4>
<p>Open-source component of eZ.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-eZPublishCommunityeZPublishCommunity"><strong> <span cla=
ss=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-eZPublishCommunity"></span> </=
strong>eZ Publish Community</h4>
<p>Open-source version of the previous edition of eZ.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-eZPublishEnterpriseeZPublishEnterprise"><strong> <span c=
lass=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-eZPublishEnterprise"></span>=
 </strong>eZ Publish Enterprise</h4>
<p>Commercial version of the previous edition of eZ.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-F">F</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-FieldField"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-li=
nk" id=3D"Glossary-Field"></span> </strong>Field</h4>
<p>The smallest unit for storing data in the content structure. A <a href=
=3D"#Glossary-Content">Content </a>item can contain multiple Fields, each o=
f them with a <a href=3D"#Glossary-FieldValue">Field Value</a>. The Field V=
alue must correspond to the <a href=3D"#Glossary-FieldType">Field Type</a> =
as defined in the <a href=3D"#Glossary-ContentType">Content Type</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-FieldTypeFieldType"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-a=
nchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-FieldType"></span> </strong>Field Type</h4>
<p>The type of data which can be stored in a <a href=3D"#Glossary-Field">Fi=
eld</a>. Field Types which make up <a href=3D"#Glossary-Cont">Content </a>a=
re defined in the <a href=3D"#Glossary-ContentType">Content Type</a>.</p>
<p>Field Type is conceptually similar to a data type in programming. Howeve=
r, the available Field Types include both simple data types (for example in=
teger or float numbers) and more complex structures (for example image, med=
ia file or binary file).</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Field+Types">Fie=
ld Types</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-FieldValueFieldValue"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence=
-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-FieldValue"></span> </strong>Field Value</h4>
<p>The value which is assigned to a <a href=3D"#Glossary-Field">Field </a>w=
hen <a href=3D"#Glossary-Content">Content </a>is created based on a <a href=
=3D"#Glossary-ContentType">Content Type</a>. The type of value is defined b=
y the <a href=3D"#Glossary-FieldType">Field Type</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-FlexworkflowFlexworkflow"><span class=3D"confluence-anch=
or-link" id=3D"Glossary-Flexworkflow"></span>Flex workflow</h4>
<p>A functionality for managing the Content review process. It allows you t=
o ask other users to review your content and send the reviewers mail notifi=
cations.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Content+review+w=
orkflow">Content review workflow</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-L">L</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-LandingPageLandingPage"><strong> <span class=3D"confluen=
ce-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-LandingPage"></span> </strong>Landing Page</=
h4>
<p>In online marketing, the part of the website that a customer is directed=
 to first when reaching a webpage through a search engine or a marketing li=
nk.</p>
<p>In eZ terms, a special form of <a href=3D"#Glossary-Content">Content</a>=
. It allows you to organize the page using specially tailored blocks of con=
tent.</p>
<p>Landing Pages can be created in <a href=3D"#Glossary-Pagemode">Page mode=
</a>.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Creating+content=
+-+Landing+Page">Creating content - Landing Page</a>.</p>
<p>More information (Technical Manual): <a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?p=
ageId=3D31430521">Landing Page Field Type (Enterprise)</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-LayoutLayout"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-=
link" id=3D"Glossary-Layout"></span> </strong>Layout</h4>
<p>The way in which a <a href=3D"#Glossary-LandingPage">Landing Page</a> is=
 divided into <a href=3D"#Glossary-Zone">zones</a>. Each zone can contain a=
 number of <a href=3D"#Glossary-Block">blocks</a>. See also <a href=3D"#Glo=
ssary-Dynamicpage">Dynamic page</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-LegacyLegacy"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-=
link" id=3D"Glossary-Legacy"></span> </strong>Legacy</h4>
<p>General term for previous versions of eZ, from 3.x to 5.x.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-LocationLocation"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anc=
hor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Location"></span> </strong>Location</h4>
<p>The place in which <a href=3D"#Glossary-Content">Content </a>is located =
in the content structure, indicated by a Location ID. A Content item can be=
 assigned to more than one Location (have more than one Location ID), but a=
 single Location ID can have only one Content item in it.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Content+Location=
s">Content Locations</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-M">M</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-MarketingAutomationMarketingAutomation"><strong> <span c=
lass=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-MarketingAutomation"></span>=
 </strong>Marketing Automation</h4>
<p>A part of <a href=3D"#Glossary-CloudServices">Cloud Services</a> offerin=
g marketing automation capabilities: functionalities for generating and man=
aging leads and sales management.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-MedialibraryMedialibrary"><strong> <span class=3D"conflu=
ence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Medialibrary"></span> </strong>Media libra=
ry</h4>
<p>The place where all media (for example images, videos, etc.) are stored =
in the content structure. When choosing a piece of media to place in your c=
ontent, you will use the <a href=3D"#Glossary-UniversalDiscoveryWidget">Uni=
versal Discovery Widget</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-MultisitesetupMultisitesetup"><strong> <span class=3D"co=
nfluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Multisitesetup"></span>Multisite setup=
</strong></h4>
<p>A configuration where one eZ installation serves multiple websites (for =
example, different versions of a company website for different internationa=
l markets).</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-N">N</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-NodeNode"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"G=
lossary-Node"></span> <em>Node</em></h4>
<p>Legacy term for <a href=3D"#Glossary-Location">Location</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-O">O</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-Object-orientedcontentstructureObject-orientedcontentstr=
ucture"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Obje=
ct-orientedcontentstructure"></span> </strong>Object-oriented content struc=
ture</h4>
<p>The fundamental idea behind structuring content in eZ. Based on the conc=
epts of object-oriented programming, this structure treats every Content it=
em as an object, an instance of a predefined <a href=3D"#Glossary-ContentTy=
pe">Content Type</a>, with a number of <a href=3D"#Glossary-Field">Fields <=
/a>reflecting its properties.</p>
<p>See <a href=3D"#Glossary-Content">Content</a>, <a href=3D"#Glossary-Cont=
entType">Content Type</a>, <a href=3D"#Glossary-Field">Field</a>, <a href=
=3D"#Glossary-FieldType">Field Type</a>.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Fundamental+conc=
epts">Fundamental concepts</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-P">P</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-PagemodePagemode"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anc=
hor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Pagemode"></span> </strong>Page mode</h4>
<p>The editing mode available in <a href=3D"#Glossary-eZEnterprise">eZ Ente=
rprise</a>. Allows you to plan, create and modify content live, while previ=
ewing the effects of the changes in real time.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Page+mode+interf=
ace">Page mode interface</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-PerformancemodePerformancemode"><span class=3D"confluenc=
e-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Performancemode"></span>Performance mode</h4>
<p>The editing mode available in <a href=3D"#Glossary-CloudServices">Cloud =
Services</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-PermissionsPermissions"><strong> <span class=3D"confluen=
ce-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Permissions"></span> </strong>Permissions</h=
4>
<p>See <a href=3D"#Glossary-Policy">Policies</a>, <a href=3D"#Glossary-Role=
">Roles</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-PolicyPolicy"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-=
link" id=3D"Glossary-Policy"></span> </strong>Policy</h4>
<p>The basic element of the permissions system: a rule defining access to o=
ne functionality of one module (for example modifying articles), with possi=
ble further limitations. Can be assigned to <a href=3D"#Glossary-Useraccoun=
t">users </a>and <a href=3D"#Glossary-Usergroup">user groups</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-PublicAPIPublicAPI"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-a=
nchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-PublicAPI"></span> </strong>Public API</h4>
<p>A PHP API which exposes a&nbsp;Repository, allowing you to create, read,=
 update, manage and delete all objects available in eZ, both Content and re=
lated objects such as Sections, Locations, Content Types etc.</p>
<p>More information (Technical Manual): <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Publi=
c+API+Guide">Public API Guide</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-R">R</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-RecommendationRecommendation"><strong> <span class=3D"co=
nfluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Recommendation"></span> </strong>Recom=
mendation</h4>
<p>A part of <a href=3D"#Glossary-CloudServices">Cloud Services</a> contain=
ing an engine for gathering customer information and presenting recommendat=
ions. Powered by <a href=3D"https://yoochoose.com/" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">YOOCHOOSE!</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-RepositoryRepository"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence=
-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Repository"></span> </strong>Repository</h4>
<p>Storage place for all content in an eZ installation. It can be interacte=
d with using the public API.</p>
<p>Can also refer to a GitHub repository (eZ uses GitHub to <a href=3D"http=
s://github.com/ezsystems/ezplatform" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">store and share its open-source code</a>).</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-RESTAPIRESTAPI"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-ancho=
r-link" id=3D"Glossary-RESTAPI"></span> </strong>REST API</h4>
<p>An API which allows you to interact with an eZ installation using the HT=
TP protocol, following a <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer" rel=3D"nofollow">REST</a> in=
teraction model.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-RoleRole"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link=
" id=3D"Glossary-Role"></span> </strong>Role</h4>
<p>An element of the permissions system: a collection of <a href=3D"#Glossa=
ry-Policy">Policies </a>assigned to a particular user function (for example=
 a sports section editor). Can be assigned to <a href=3D"#Glossary-User">Us=
ers </a>and <a href=3D"#Glossary-Usergroup">User groups</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-S">S</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-SectionSection"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-ancho=
r-link" id=3D"Glossary-Section"></span> </strong>Section</h4>
<p>A demarcated part of the <a href=3D"#Glossary-Contenttree">Content tree<=
/a>. Sections can be used to control permissions granted to users (for exam=
ple, a "Sports Editors" group can be assigned Roles which only grant access=
 to the "Sports" Section of website).</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Managing+Section=
s">Managing Sections</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ServicelifeServicelife"><strong> <span class=3D"confluen=
ce-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Servicelife"></span> </strong>Service life</=
h4>
<p>Support and maintenance cycle of different versions of eZ. See <a href=
=3D"https://support.ez.no/Public/Service-Life" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">https://support.ez.no/Public/Service-Life</a> for detailed in=
formation.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-SiteaccessSiteaccess"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence=
-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Siteaccess"></span> </strong>Siteaccess</h4>
<p>A collection of configuration settings provided when accessing a website=
. A single site can have multiple siteaccesses which define the content and=
 design of the page that will be displayed. This functionality can be used =
for example to create separate versions of the website for visitors and for=
 administrators.</p>
<p>More information (Technical Manual): <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/SiteA=
ccess">SiteAccess</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-SmartAnalyticsSmartAnalytics"><span class=3D"confluence-=
anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-SmartAnalytics"></span>Smart Analytics</h4>
<p>A part of <a href=3D"#Glossary-CloudServices">Cloud Services</a> contain=
ing an engine for tracking and analyzing visitor behavior on the website.</=
p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-StashStash"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-li=
nk" id=3D"Glossary-Stash"></span> </strong>Stash</h4>
<p>An open-source technology used for caching. See&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://w=
ww.stashphp.com/index.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http:/=
/www.stashphp.com/index.html</a>.</p>
<p class=3D"confluence-link">More information (Technical Manual): <span cla=
ss=3D"confluence-link"><span class=3D"confluence-link"><a href=3D"/display/=
DEVELOPER/Repository#Repository-PersistenceCache">Persistence cache</a></sp=
an></span>, <span class=3D"confluence-link"><a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/R=
epository#Repository-Persistencecacheconfiguration">Persistence cache confi=
guration</a></span>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-StudioStudio"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-=
link" id=3D"Glossary-Studio"></span> </strong>Studio</h4>
<p>Commercial component of eZ, together with <a href=3D"#Glossary-eZPlatfor=
m">eZ Platform</a> it constitutes <a href=3D"#Glossary-eZEnterprise">eZ Ent=
erprise</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-StudioToolbarStudioToolbar"><strong> <span class=3D"conf=
luence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-StudioToolbar"></span> </strong>Studio T=
oolbar<strong> <br> </strong></h4>
<p>An action toolbar at the top of the screen in <a href=3D"#Glossary-Studi=
o">Studio</a> which allows you to create, edit and view content.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Page+mode+interf=
ace">Page mode interface</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-SymfonySymfony"><em> <strong> <span class=3D"confluence-=
anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Symfony"></span> </strong> </em>Symfony</h4>
<p>A PHP framework for web applications and a set of reusable PHP component=
s. eZ has been using Symfony as its framework since eZ Publish 5.0. See <a =
href=3D"https://symfony.com/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http=
s://symfony.com/</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-T">T</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-TemplateTemplate"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anc=
hor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Template"></span> </strong>Template</h4>
<p>An instrument for customizing the visual aspect of a website. A template=
 is applied to the content and defines the layout, themes and other graphic=
al features with which content will be displayed on the page. eZ uses <a hr=
ef=3D"#Glossary-Twig">Twig </a>as its main template engine.</p>
<p>More information (Technical Manual): <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Desig=
n">Design</a>, <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Content+Rendering">Content Ren=
dering</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-TwigTwig"><em> <strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor=
-link" id=3D"Glossary-Twig"></span> </strong> </em>Twig</h4>
<p>A PHP <a href=3D"#Glossary-Template">template </a>engine used as the mai=
n template engine in current versions of eZ. See <a href=3D"http://twig.sen=
siolabs.org/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://twig.sensiola=
bs.org/</a> for more information.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-U">U</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-UniversalDiscoveryWidgetUniversalDiscoveryWidget(UDW)"><=
strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-UniversalDisc=
overyWidget"></span> </strong>Universal Discovery Widget (UDW)</h4>
<p>A tool for browsing, searching and selecting content in the <a href=3D"#=
Glossary-Contenttree">Content tree</a> and <a href=3D"#Glossary-Medialibrar=
y">Media library</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-UserUser"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link=
" id=3D"Glossary-User"></span> </strong>User</h4>
<p>An account in which information about a user is contained in the system.=
</p>
<p>Technically, a User is a Content item of a special <a href=3D"#Glossary-=
ContentType">Content Type</a>.</p>
<p>More information (User Guide): <a href=3D"/display/USER/Managing+Users">=
Managing Users</a>.</p>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-UsergroupUsergroup"><strong> <span class=3D"confluence-a=
nchor-link" id=3D"Glossary-Usergroup"></span> </strong>User group</h4>
<p>A collection of users grouped together for efficiency reasons. You can a=
ssign <a href=3D"#Glossary-Policy">policies </a>and <a href=3D"#Glossary-Ro=
le">roles </a>to User groups as well as individual <a href=3D"#Glossary-Use=
r">Users</a>.</p>
<p>Technically, a User group is a Content item of a special <a href=3D"#Glo=
ssary-ContentType">Content Type</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-X">X</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-XMLXML"><em> <strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor-l=
ink" id=3D"Glossary-XML"></span> </strong> </em>XML</h4>
<p>A markup language for encoding documents (short for Extensible Markup La=
nguage). One of the formats for storing configuration data in eZ, as well a=
s an output form for REST API.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-Y">Y</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-YAMLYAML"><em> <strong> <span class=3D"confluence-anchor=
-link" id=3D"Glossary-YAML"></span> </strong> </em>YAML</h4>
<p>A data serialization language (short for YAML Ain't Markup Language). On=
e of the formats for storing configuration data in eZ.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Glossary-Z">Z</h2>
<h4 id=3D"Glossary-ZoneZone"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"G=
lossary-Zone"></span>Zone</h4>
<p><span class=3D"DEF"> <span class=3D"DEF">A basic part of a <a href=3D"#G=
lossary-LandingPage">Landing Page</a> layout. Zones are are deployed over a=
 <a href=3D"#Glossary-Layout">layout </a>in a particular position</span> </=
span> and can in turn contain <a href=3D"#Glossary-Block">blocks</a>.</p>
